DialogText:
As you're standing here right now, you can imagine what we have decided on, to create The Kingdom of Gods! A construction so grand, mankind would never see such a sight once they've set foot in the kingdom.

Not any request is turned over so quickly. We have also given this generation a proposal - to never contact us again, even at times of desperate need, The Obelisk will forever stay dormant. The proposal accepted by the generation as a noble sacrifice.

Another proposal for this undetaking was also made. To pay your debt in the world's time. An ethereal clock, ticking down the days until total obliteration, this is The Rapture. Once the clock chimes, the world will be torn to shreds, and all believers will be ascended to the kingdom.

The proposal reluctantly accepted by the generation as an unfortunate sacrifice,
